This paper focuses on user identification using motion dynamics captured by sensors in smartphones. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it deals with how users interact with technology. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for classification suggests that it could also fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG).
